cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Consumer Research Bench (CRB): Evaluating AI Agents for Consumer Research"
message: "If you use CRB, please cite it as below."
type: dataset
authors:
  - name: "Independent CRB Working Group"
version: "0.6"
date-released: "2026-06-22"
license: CC-BY-4.0
url: "https://crb-bench.org"
repository-code: "https://github.com/REPLACE_ME/crb"
abstract: >-
  Consumer Research Bench (CRB) is a benchmark for evaluating AI agents on
  consumer research tasks. It defines its construct as decision-ready
  consumer-research quality per unit time, at a fixed evidence-grounding bar.
  CRB uses two scored tracks — an Objective Track scored against expert-worked
  ground truth, and a Report Track scored by C-RACE, a reference-based,
  criteria-adaptive framework validated against human experts — plus
  RetroSignals, a frozen consumer-signal environment enabling a data x model
  ablation. CRB is designed to be administered independently. Working Draft v0.6
  (preprint); results pending first run.
keywords:
  - benchmark
  - consumer research
  - LLM evaluation
  - deep research agents
  - market intelligence
